Introduction

SUPERNOVA (Korean: 슈퍼노바; Japanese: 超新星), formerly known as Choshinsung, is a five-member South Korean boy group under SV Entertainment. They made their official debut in 2007 with the digital single "Hit." Since 2012, the group's activities are mostly focused on Japan.
